The paper deals with the problem of recovering low-rank tensors corrupted by sparse errors, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. The paper proposes a new method based on convex optimization and tensor singular value decomposition. The paper also includes numerical experiments and an application to image denoising. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization, which suggests the possibility of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as potential sub-categories.
